function.arguments:

  'HP:0000491',  // Keratitis
  'HP:0032163',  // Molluscum contagiosum
  'HP:0006532',  // Recurrent pneumonia
  'HP:0000403',  // Recurrent otitis media
  'HP:0100658',  // Cellulitis
  'HP:0410330',  // Meat allergen allergy
  'HP:0410328',  // Egg allergy
  'HP:0006335',  // Persistence of primary teeth
  'HP:0410017',  // Otitis externa
  'HP:0410331',  // Nut food product allergy
  'HP:0000246',  // Sinusitis
  'HP:0002788',  // Recurrent upper respiratory tract infections
  'HP:0410327'   // Dairy allergy
] WITH d, count(p) AS match_count ORDER BY match_count DESC LIMIT 20
OPTIONAL MATCH (d)-[:biolink_has_phenotype]->(p2:biolink_PhenotypicFeature) WHERE p2.id IN ['HP:0410323', 'HP:0002099', 'HP:0002664'] // Excluded features: Drug allergy, Asthma, Neoplasm
WITH d, match_count, collect(p2) AS excluded_features WHERE size(excluded_features) = 0
RETURN d.id AS disease_id, d.name AS disease_name, match_count ORDER BY match_count DESC LIMIT 10"}

messages.content:
Based on the patient's features (multiple allergies, recurrent infections, skin findings, and persistence of primary teeth) and the exclusion of drug allergy, asthma, and neoplasm, here is a rank-ordered list of the most likely diagnoses from the Monarch knowledge graph:

1. [Leukocyte adhesion deficiency type II](https://monarchinitiative.org/MONDO:0009953) (4 matching features)
2. [Hyper-IgE recurrent infection syndrome 1, autosomal dominant (Job syndrome)](https://monarchinitiative.org/MONDO:0007818) (4 matching features)
3. [WHIM syndrome 1](https://monarchinitiative.org/MONDO:8000006) (4 matching features)
4. [Fusariosis](https://monarchinitiative.org/MONDO:0016426) (4 matching features)
5. [Idiopathic CD4 lymphocytopenia](https://monarchinitiative.org/MONDO:0014226) (3 matching features)
6. [Felty syndrome](https://monarchinitiative.org/MONDO:0007603) (3 matching features)
7. [Trichorhinophalangeal syndrome type II](https://monarchinitiative.org/MONDO:0007874) (3 matching features)
8. [Combined immunodeficiency due to STK4 deficiency](https://monarchinitiative.org/MONDO:0013934) (3 matching features)
9. [Deficiency in anterior pituitary function - variable immunodeficiency syndrome](https://monarchinitiative.org/MONDO:0017407) (3 matching features)
10. [Macrocephaly, neurodevelopmental delay, lymphoid hyperplasia, and persistent fetal hemoglobin](https://monarchinitiative.org/MONDO:0859231) (3 matching features)

The most likely diagnosis, given the combination of recurrent infections, atopic/allergic features, and persistence of primary teeth, is Hyper-IgE recurrent infection syndrome (Job syndrome), but Leukocyte adhesion deficiency type II and WHIM syndrome are also strong considerations. Further clinical and laboratory evaluation would be needed for confirmation.
